feed.title: Croajingalong NP - Plants
feed.subtitle: Including Mallacoota. Initial flora list supplied by Parks Victoria.

entry.title: Cotula coronopifolia
entry.content: Taller than usual and with undivided leaves.

entry.title: Polyscias sambucifolia subsp. 1
entry.content: Broadest leaves I've seen on this taxon.

entry.title: Schoenus spp.
entry.content: Flowers on long stalks. Possibly S. brevifolius.

entry.title: Comesperma defoliatum
entry.content: About 50cm tall, leafless, often with just one flower.

entry.title: Epacris paludosa
entry.content: On the 2nd pic the glabrous style can be seen, which distinguishes it from the otherwise almost identical E. lanuginosa.

entry.title: Blechnum minus
entry.content: Young plant - looks like a Pellaea but isn't.

entry.title: Sannantha pluriflora
entry.content: Used to be Baeckea virgata and has recently changed name again from Babingtonia pluriflora (via Babingtonia virgata) to Sannantha pluriflora!

entry.title: Goodenia humilis
entry.content: All plants here had red in upper petals. This occurs sometimes in G. humilis.

entry.title: Candalides hyacinthina hyacinthina, Lobelia gibbosa s.s.
Lobelia gibbosa s.s.
entry.content: First time I've been able to ID this species. Leaves not obviously lobed (so not L. dentata). Under the microscope, seed was 0.2-0.3mm long, reticulate, not 3-angled (so not L. simplicicaulis).
